1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,760
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:06,760
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:11,000
My name is Katrin and today we have an elementary level lesson for you.
我是Katrin，今天我们为大家准备了一节初级课程。

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,600
This one is especially for people who are interested in babies.
这节课程特别适合对宝宝感兴趣的人。

5
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,600
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:19,480
Maybe you have a baby, you will have a baby, maybe you're pregnant and this is a great
也许你有宝宝，或者即将有宝宝，又或者你怀孕了，这节课程非常棒，

7
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:23,200
lesson for that because we are talking about a baby shower.
因为我们讨论的是宝宝派对。

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:27,560
Okay, so before we get started, let's take a look at vocabulary preview and learn what
好的，在开始之前，我们先来看看词汇预览，了解一下

9
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:31,000
exactly a baby shower is.
宝宝派对到底是什么。

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,440
Okay, so a baby shower.
好的，宝宝派对。

12
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:38,760
You would think that this is about bathing the baby, about giving the baby a bath.
你可能会以为这是关于给宝宝洗澡的。

13
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:40,680
No, not a real shower.
不，不是真正的淋浴。

14
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:44,520
A baby shower or a bridal shower, these are parties.
宝宝派对或新娘派对，这些都是派对。

15
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:46,120
Okay, they're parties.
没错，它们是派对。

16
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:53,280
And in this case, a baby shower is a party that you throw for a woman that is pregnant,
在这种情况下，宝宝派对是为怀孕的女性举办的派对，

17
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,280
right?
对吧？

18
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,280
That's right.
没错。

19
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:59,800
So if my sister is going to have a baby, I throw her a baby shower.
所以如果我姐姐要生宝宝了，我会为她举办一个宝宝派对。

20
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,960
It's a party where all of her friends give her gifts.
这是一个派对，她所有的朋友都会送她礼物。

21
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:03,960
Okay.
好的。

22
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:06,120
Yeah, it's a way to celebrate having a baby.
是的，这是一种庆祝生宝宝的方式。

23
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:12,080
Okay, so they give her gifts, you'll play games as well as to like maybe guess the name
好的，所以他们会送她礼物，还会玩游戏，比如猜宝宝的名字

24
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:14,640
of the baby or guess the sex of the baby.
或猜宝宝的性别。

25
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:15,640
Exactly.
没错。

26
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:16,640
Stuff like that.
诸如此类的事情。

27
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:17,840
Okay, so it's a very common thing.
好的，所以这是很常见的事情。

28
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:20,440
I think it's mostly for women.
我觉得这主要是为女性举办的。

29
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:24,040
I don't really know if men have baby showers as well.
我不太确定男性是否也有宝宝派对。

30
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,040
I don't think so.
我觉得没有。

31
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,040
I don't think so either.
我也觉得没有。

32
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:30,640
But it's a very popular tradition in the United States and many other parts of the world.
但这是美国以及世界许多地方非常流行的传统。

33
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:32,600
So we're going to talk about that.
所以我们要讨论这个。

34
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:41,760
Let's listen to the dialogue for the first time.
让我们第一次听对话。

35
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:44,760
Thank you for organizing this great baby shower for me.
谢谢你为我组织这个很棒的宝宝派对。

36
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:48,560
I've always been to baby showers but never actually had one held for me.
我一直参加别人的宝宝派对，但从来没人为我举办过。

37
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,120
Let's get started.
我们开始吧。

38
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:53,000
Okay, let's start opening some presents.
好的，我们开始拆一些礼物吧。

39
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Oh, look, what a great little bib for the baby.
哦，看，多好的宝宝围兜啊。

40
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,760
This will definitely come in handy.
这肯定会派上用场。

41
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:02,080
Oh, wow, you also got me a stroller.
哦，哇，你还给我买了婴儿车。

42
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,360
That's so great.
太棒了。

43
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,640
Thank you.
谢谢你。

44
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,280
This next one is from Betty.
下一个是Betty送的。

45
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,000
A high chair and a car seat.
一个高脚椅和一个汽车安全座椅。

46
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,160
Wow, Betty, thank you so much.
哇，Betty，非常感谢你。

47
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:13,080
I really appreciate it.
我真的很感激。

48
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,200
One more from Carla.
还有一个是Carla送的。

49
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,280
A playpen and crib.
一个游戏围栏和婴儿床。

50
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,280
Thanks, Carla.
谢谢，Carla。

51
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,960
This is just what I needed.
这正是我需要的。

52
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,100
Okay, that's all of them.
好的，就这些了。

53
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,640
No more gifts.
没有更多礼物了。

54
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:26,440
Now who wants to guess when the baby is due?
现在谁来猜猜宝宝什么时候出生？

55
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:29,400
I think my water just broke.
我想我的羊水破了。

56
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:36,160
Get me to a hospital.
快送我去医院。

57
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,840
All right, so very interesting.
好的，非常有趣。

58
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:44,960
All the gifts that they got and definitely very useful because this is a very common
他们收到的所有礼物都非常有用，因为这些都是给宝宝准备的

59
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:47,120
items that you get for babies, right?
常见物品，对吧？

60
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,120
That's right.
没错。

61
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:53,120
This stuff is really, really valuable because if you have a baby or if your brother or sister
这些东西真的非常宝贵，因为如果你有宝宝，或者你的兄弟或姐妹

62
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:56,600
has a baby, you'll notice that these are very common items.
有宝宝，你会发现这些都是很常见的物品。

63
00:02:56,600 --> 00:03:02,340
So let's go through a couple of them in today's Language Takeaway.
所以让我们在今天的语言要点中看看其中几个。

64
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:03,720
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

65
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:08,300
Okay, so the first word that we're going to take a look at, the most common one and useful
好的，我们要看的第一个词，最常见也最有用

66
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,880
one for a baby is a bib.
的宝宝用品是围兜。

67
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,880
Bib.
围兜。

68
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,840
So, babies are messy.
所以，宝宝们很邋遢。

69
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,480
When they eat food, they get their food on their clothes.
他们吃东西时，会把食物弄到衣服上。

70
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,840
So to protect the clothes, babies wear bibs.
所以为了保护衣服，宝宝们会戴围兜。

71
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,840
This is a piece of cloth or fabric around their neck.
这是一块围在他们脖子上的布或织物。

72
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,160
Okay, a bib.
好的，围兜。

73
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:29,720
And also, sometimes you want to go out with your baby to the mall, you're walking and
还有，有时候你想带宝宝去商场，你走着走着，

74
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:33,000
you don't want to carry him in your arms all the time.
不想一直抱着他。

75
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,080
So you need a stroller.
所以你需要一辆婴儿车。

76
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:40,200
Okay, so basically a stroller is a chair on wheels for a baby.
好的，所以婴儿车基本上就是带轮子的宝宝椅子。

77
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,200
Babies are heavy and as they get older, they get heavier.
宝宝很重，而且随着他们长大，会越来越重。

78
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:46,960
And so this is a way to push the baby around, not carry the baby.
所以这是一种推着宝宝走的方式，而不是抱着宝宝。

79
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:51,040
Right, and maybe the baby falls asleep, so they can fall asleep in the stroller.
对，而且宝宝可能会睡着，所以他们可以在婴儿车里睡觉。

80
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,040
Exactly.
没错。

81
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,680
Okay, and while talking about chairs, we're going to take a look at two different types
好的，说到椅子，我们来看看两种不同类型的椅子。

82
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,060
of chairs.
椅子。

83
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:58,960
First one is a high chair.
第一种是高脚椅。

84
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,480
Okay, high chair.
好的，高脚椅。

85
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:03,560
Think about the word high, that means tall in this case.
想想“高”这个词，这里指的是高的意思。

86
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:07,700
A high chair is a chair for babies at the table.
高脚椅是给婴儿在餐桌旁用的椅子。

87
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:11,480
So if you put a baby on a regular chair, they can't eat with adults.
所以如果你把婴儿放在普通椅子上，他们没法跟大人一起吃饭。

88
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,560
Right, they're too small.
对，他们太小了。

89
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:17,040
So we give them high chairs so that they can sit a little bit higher and they can be at
所以我们给他们高脚椅，这样他们可以坐得高一点，就能跟大人一起在餐桌旁。

90
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,440
the table with adults.
跟大人一起在餐桌旁。

91
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,440
Exactly.
没错。

92
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:21,060
So they're very common.
所以它们很常见。

93
00:04:21,060 --> 00:04:25,000
For example, you go to a restaurant, they will have a little high chairs if you have
比如，你去餐厅，如果你有婴儿或小孩，他们会有小高脚椅。

94
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,160
a baby or a small child.
有婴儿或小孩。

95
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:30,040
So if you're at a restaurant, you have a baby, you ask for a high chair.
所以如果你在餐厅，带着婴儿，你可以要一把高脚椅。

96
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:32,240
You say, do you have a high chair, please?
你会说，请问你们有高脚椅吗？

97
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,420
Yeah, perfect.
对，完美。

98
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:39,200
And well, if you're going to the restaurant or you go anywhere in your car, you need to
嗯，如果你要去餐厅或者开车去任何地方，你需要确保婴儿安全，显然他们没法坐在普通座位上。

99
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:44,600
have the baby be safe and obviously they can't fit on a normal seat.
没法坐在普通座位上。

100
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,600
No, with a seat belt?
用安全带也不行吗？

101
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,800
No, I don't think so.
不，我觉得不行。

102
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,160
So that's why you get them a car seat.
所以这就是为什么你要给他们买汽车安全座椅。

103
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:57,240
Okay, a car seat is a special chair that goes on the seat of the car and usually it's very,
好的，汽车安全座椅是一种特殊的椅子，放在汽车座位上，通常非常非常安全。

104
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,240
very safe.
非常安全。

105
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,840
It's made to protect the baby.
它是为了保护婴儿而设计的。

106
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:01,840
Right.
对。

107
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:06,320
So if you are ever in a car accident, the car seat will help protect the small baby.
所以如果你遇到车祸，汽车安全座椅能帮助保护小婴儿。

108
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,320
Right.
对。

109
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:10,360
So it's supposed to go in the back of the car, not the front.
所以它应该放在汽车后座，而不是前座。

110
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,800
Yes, always.
是的，总是这样。

111
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,800
Very good.
非常好。

112
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:16,040
And now moving on to our last two words.
现在来看最后两个词。

113
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:21,540
If you're at home, you sometimes want to have the baby play and you get them a play pen.
如果你在家，有时想让婴儿玩耍，你会给他们一个游戏围栏。

114
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:26,720
So basically this is a way for parents to leave the baby playing but not look at the
所以这基本上是一种让父母可以放婴儿在里面玩，但不用一直盯着看的方式。

115
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,720
baby the whole time.
不用一直盯着看。

116
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,720
Right.
对。

117
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:34,020
A play pen is like a cage for a baby, but it's soft and it's cute and it's pretty.
游戏围栏就像一个婴儿的笼子，但它是软的，可爱的，漂亮的。

118
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:39,680
So it's basically like an open area that's protected on the sides and the baby can go
所以它基本上是一个开放的区域，四周有保护，婴儿可以进去，但出不来。

119
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,200
inside but the baby can't leave.
但婴儿出不来。

120
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,200
Right.
对。

121
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:48,520
It's like a cage basically and it has little toys and that's the way you just keep them
它基本上像个笼子，里面有小玩具，这样你就可以让他们在里面待一会儿。

122
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,520
in there for a while.
让他们在里面待一会儿。

123
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,520
Exactly.
没错。

124
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,520
All right.
好的。

125
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:55,400
And now when you want to put the baby to sleep, it can't obviously sleep in a big bed because
现在，当你想让婴儿睡觉时，显然他们不能睡在大床上，因为可能会滚来滚去，可能会掉下来。

126
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,680
it might roll over, it might fall off.
可能会掉下来。

127
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:00,440
There's a lot of things that can go wrong, so you get them a crib.
有很多可能出问题的地方，所以你会给他们买婴儿床。

128
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,440
Right.
对。

129
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:03,160
So a crib is a bed for babies.
所以婴儿床是给婴儿用的床。

130
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:08,200
This is usually high off the ground and it's usually quite small and the baby can't climb
它通常离地面较高，而且通常很小，婴儿爬不出来。

131
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,200
out of it.
爬不出来。

132
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,200
Right.
对。

133
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,200
Yeah.
嗯。

134
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:14,840
So it's a very safe bed so the baby can't fall out, can't climb out.
所以这是一张非常安全的床，婴儿不会掉出来，也爬不出来。

135
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:15,840
Exactly.
没错。

136
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:16,840
Very good.
非常好。

137
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:20,880
So very interesting, very useful things for you if you're having a baby, planning on getting
所以如果你有婴儿，或者打算买这些东西，这些都非常有趣、非常有用。

138
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,160
these things.
打算买这些东西。

139
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:31,120
So why don't we go back, listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back with Fluency Builder.
所以我们为什么不回去再听一遍对话，然后我们会回来做流利度练习。

140
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:34,080
Thank you for organizing this great baby shower for me.
谢谢你为我组织这个很棒的宝宝派对。

141
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:37,880
I've always been to baby showers but never actually had one held for me.
我以前参加过宝宝派对，但从来没人为我办过。

142
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,440
Let's get started.
我们开始吧。

143
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,480
Okay.
好的。

144
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,360
Let's start opening some presents.
我们开始拆礼物吧。

145
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:46,320
Oh look, what a great little bib for the baby.
哦看，多好的小围兜啊，给婴儿的。

146
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,080
This will definitely come in handy.
这肯定很实用。

147
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,400
Oh wow, you also got me a stroller.
哦哇，你还给我买了婴儿推车。

148
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,720
That's so great.
太棒了。

149
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:53,960
Thank you.
谢谢你。

150
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,600
This next one is from Betty.
下一个是贝蒂送的。

151
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,320
A high chair and a car seat.
一个高脚椅和一个汽车安全座椅。

152
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:00,480
Wow, Betty, thank you so much.
哇，贝蒂，太感谢你了。

153
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,400
I really appreciate it.
我真的很感激。

154
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,520
One more from Carla.
还有一个是卡拉送的。

155
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,240
A playpen and crib.
一个游戏围栏和婴儿床。

156
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,440
Thanks, Carla.
谢谢，卡拉。

157
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,280
This is just what I needed.
这正是我需要的。

158
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,400
Okay, that's all of them.
好了，就这些了。

159
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,960
No more gifts.
没有更多礼物了。

160
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:16,560
Now who wants to guess when the baby is due?
现在谁来猜猜预产期是什么时候？

